AAR CY 2016, Part II, No. 3 | 18.  The unspent LDRRMF as of December 31,2018 totaling P960,304.65 were not transferred to the Special Trust Fund, subsidiary ledgers on prior years’ balances were not maintained, monthly reports on LDRRMF utilization were erroneous and composition of the unutilized portion of the LDRRMF were not presented in the Notes to Financial Statements, contrary to COA Circular No. 2012-002, thus, the funds may be used for other purposes and the Municipality cannot determine immediately the funds available for disaster preparedness and during calamities. | We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

 63) Maintain and update subsidiary ledgers (SL) for LDRRMF in the General Fund, with separate SL for 30% QRF and for the 70% MF; 


 64) Maintain and update subsidiary ledgers for the LDRRMF Trust Fund by year of transfer or by donor, if any;

 65) Submit, with the assistance of the MDRRMO, an accurate Report on Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF, on or before the 15th day of the end of each month, to the COA Audit Team.

AAR CY 2017, Part II, No 11 | 23. The Local Council for the Protection of Children (LCPC) is not yet institutionalized in the Municipality of Culaba and no amount was appropriated in its Annual Budget for the implementation of programs, projects and activities particularly on delinquency prevention, contrary to RA No. 9344, thus, no assurance that the rights and welfare of the children in the municipality were strengthened or protected. | We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

71)  Constitute the LCPC from among its department heads, with himself as the chairman;

72) Require the created LCPC to identify programs, projects and activities for child protection and welfare and prevention of juvenile delinquency;

73) Prepare the LCPC Annual Work and Financial Plan prioritized according to needs for integration in the Local Development Plan and;

74) Ensure that funds for LCPC is equivalent to 1% of the IRA of the Municipality.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Constitute the LCPC from among its department heads, with himself as the chairman;

Require the created LCPC to identify programs, projects and activities for child protection and welfare and prevention of juvenile delinquency;

Prepare the LCPC Annual Work and Financial Plan prioritized according to needs for integration in the Local Development Plan and;

Ensure that funds for LCPC is equivalent to 1% of the IRA of the Municipality.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct:

The Inventory Committee to confirm through inspection the listed properties per Division, consolidate the list using the RPCPPE in the prescribed format duly approved by the LCE and submit the said report within the prescribed period to the offices concerned;

The Property Officer to maintain Property Cards for each kind of PPE owned by the agency and reconcile the same with accounting records, and ;

The Municipal Accountant to maintain and update the prescribed PPELC, reconcile the same monthly with property records, compute the depreciation of all depreciable PPEs and present accurately all accounts in the FS in accordance with the Revised Chart of Accounts for LGUs.

We recommend the LCE to direct the Municipal Accountant and the HRMO to:

Ensure that the net take home pay of all employees of the Municipality is not below the minimum amount prescribed by law;

Verify the paying capacity of an employee before signing loan applications so that the mandated net take home pay of the employee will be complied;

Authorize deductions only if the loan was obtained from accredited financing institutions enumerated by law.
